---
By: Han-shan Te-ch'ing
Source:
  - Title: The Clouds Should Know Me By Now
    Page: 126
    Translator: Red Pine
    Copyright: 1998
---
A single cloud envelops ten-thousand streamside pines
before my door the flowing water babbles all the time
no matter if it's day or if it's night I snore
until the bell across the bridge ends my blissful dreams
